Description:
Server details such server name and version and technology used are displayed in the response.

Impact:
The attacker can use these details for further exploitation specific to that server or technology used.

Steps to reproduce:
1.Open the application.
2.Capture Application Trafic using Proxy
3.It is observed that server details are shown.

Fix Recommendations:
Server details (server name and version details) and technology used should not be transmitted in the request/response messages.

 

Solution for the Fix

 

Step 1:

 

In Conf folder Open the server.xml

 

<Connector port="8080" protocol="HTTP/1.1" server="Quality Insight Bots"
               connectionTimeout="20000"
               redirectPort="8443"
                />

 Add the sever attribute in the connector tag. and reset the server. Now check the header value in the chrome browser. In the server tage it show Quality Insight Bots

 

Step 2 :

 

For Remove the Version for Apache Tomcat

 

In the Tomcat Server go to folder lib

Create a folders org/apache/catalina/util

Create a file called ServerInfo.properties 

Add the String in the file 

server.info=Apache Tomcat Version X

Save the File

Reset the Tomcat server

Check the Error Page , it will show the text Apache Tomcat Version X
